<div dir="ltr"><div><div><div><div><div>So overall the install seems to be working ok, but you might want to try a reboot to make sure everything comes up ok on reboot.  I have found that cloud sometimes requires some changes to the systemd service scripts; in particular, if the afns1 or the oraxx containers don&#39;t start on boot, and/or the switches sx1 and sw1 dont&#39; start on boot, in the cloud, you may need to go to<br><br></div>/etc/systemd/system<br><br></div>and change the e.g. sw.service files from &quot;oneshot&quot; to &quot;idle&quot; type services.  I&#39;ve already coded this in for AWS cloud, but do not have it coded for CloudAtCost yet, and have not had a chance yet to test if it should just be recoded to &quot;idle&quot; for on-premise as well.  &quot;oneshot&quot; works for on-premise, but doesn&#39;t work right for cloud setups where &quot;cloud-init&quot; is in use, which is typical of cloud bootups.  So if stuff doesn&#39;t start on boot, try making that change in the service files:<br><br>kmw@Orabuntu-LXC:~$ cd /etc/systemd/system<br>kmw@Orabuntu-LXC:/etc/systemd/system$ ls -lrt<br>total 100<br>drwxr-xr-x 2 root root 4096 Apr 16 02:13 network-online.target.wants<br>drwxr-xr-x 2 root root 4096 Apr 16 02:13 getty.target.wants<br>drwxr-xr-x 2 root root 4096 Apr 16 02:13 default.target.wants<br>lrwxrwxrwx 1 root root   35 Apr 16 02:13 syslog.service -&gt; /lib/systemd/system/rsyslog.service<br>drwxr-xr-x 2 root root 4096 Apr 16 02:28 graphical.target.wants<br>lrwxrwxrwx 1 root root   38 Apr 16 02:29 iscsi.service -&gt; /lib/systemd/system/open-iscsi.service<br>drwxr-xr-x 2 root root 4096 Apr 16 02:30 sysinit.target.wants<br>drwxr-xr-x 2 root root 4096 Apr 16 02:31 paths.target.wants<br>lrwxrwxrwx 1 root root   31 Apr 16 02:31 sshd.service -&gt; /lib/systemd/system/ssh.service<br>drwxr-xr-x 2 root root 4096 Apr 16 02:32 timers.target.wants<br>drwxr-xr-x 2 root root 4096 Apr 16 02:32 final.target.wants<br>-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  201 Apr 16 03:13 60-olxc.service<br><b>-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  268 Apr 16 03:14 sw1.service<br>-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  248 Apr 16 11:14 sx1.service<br>-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  337 Apr 16 11:15 afns1.service<br>-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  350 Apr 16 11:34 ora66c10.service<br>-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  350 Apr 16 11:36 ora66c11.service<br>-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  350 Apr 16 11:37 ora66c12.service</b><br>drwxr-xr-x 2 root root 4096 Apr 16 11:41 sockets.target.wants<br>-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  201 Apr 16 11:41 sw2.service<br>-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  201 Apr 16 11:47 sw3.service<br>-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  201 Apr 16 11:47 sw4.service<br>-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  201 Apr 16 11:47 sw5.service<br>-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  201 Apr 16 11:48 sw6.service<br>-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  201 Apr 16 11:48 sw7.service<br>-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  201 Apr 16 11:48 sw8.service<br>-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  201 Apr 16 11:48 sw9.service<br>drwxr-xr-x 2 root root 4096 Apr 16 11:48 multi-user.target.wants<br>kmw@Orabuntu-LXC:/etc/systemd/system$ cat sw1.service<br>[Unit]<br>Description=sw1 Service<br>Wants=network-online.target<br>After=network-online.target<br><br>[Service]<br>Type=<b>oneshot   &lt;-- change this to &quot;idle&quot;</b><br>User=root<br>RemainAfterExit=yes<br>ExecStart=/etc/network/openvswitch/crt_ovs_sw1.sh<br>ExecStop=/usr/bin/ovs-vsctl del-br sw1<br><br>[Install]<br>WantedBy=multi-user.target<br>kmw@Orabuntu-LXC:/etc/systemd/system$ <br><br></div>After you make the change to the service files, then you need to do:<br><br></div>sudo systemctl daemon-reload<br><br></div>and then can try a reboot again and see if they start properly on boot.<br><div><div><div><br></div></div></div></div><div class="gmail_extra"><br><div class="gmail_quote">On Sun, Apr 22, 2018 at 10:59 AM, Kenneth Wyrick <span dir="ltr">&lt;<a href="mailto:kmw@caltek.net" target="_blank">kmw@caltek.net</a>&gt;</span> wrote:<br><blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="margin:0 0 0 .8ex;border-left:1px #ccc solid;padding-left:1ex"><br>
